comment.narrative:
1. The Law of the Republic of Uzbekistan on “Water and Water Use” adopted 6 May, 1993 and requires improvement;
2. Domestic water supply and wastewater facilities suffer from lack of financing for upgrades, and operation and maintenance on a scale comparable to that of irrigation systems. The ground water in the basin is suitable for drinking use only in the Samarqand province, as further downstream its mineralization and rigidity grows. In the territory of Navoi and Bukhara provinces the chemical composition of ground water makes it unusable for drinking;
3. Uzbekistan faces consequences of the climate change as well as the threats of catastrophes in the near future. Exhaustion and pollution of water resources and as consequence, destruction of ecosystems, becomes the real threat of all mankind’s existence.  Growing demand for water among different users becomes main limiting factor for country’s development.

